// Figure 4.6: Module Federation Runtime Composition
// Host → RemoteEntry resolution → inject/unmount lifecycle

// ==================== ACTORS ====================
Browser [icon: chrome, color: blue]
Host Shell [icon: home, color: green]
Registry [icon: list, color: orange]
Remote Entry [icon: file-code, color: purple]
Remote Module [icon: box, color: cyan]

// ==================== RUNTIME COMPOSITION FLOW ====================
Browser > Host Shell : Navigate to /store/*
Host Shell > Registry : getMicroFrontendConfig('store')
Registry > Host Shell : { remoteName, exposedModule, urls }
Host Shell > Remote Entry : Fetch remoteEntry.js
Remote Entry > Host Shell : Module Federation manifest
Host Shell > Remote Module : loadRemote('store/ConsoleMicroApp')
Remote Module > Host Shell : { inject, unmount }
Host Shell > Browser : Mount remote into container

// ==================== UNMOUNT LIFECYCLE ====================
// On navigation away:
// Host Shell > Remote Module : unmount()
// Host Shell > Browser : Clean container

// ==================== KEY COMPONENTS ====================
// microFrontendRegistry.ts: Central registry
// MicroFrontendApp.tsx: Dynamic loader component
// ConsoleMicroApp: Standardized exposed module
